oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Assessing fire damage
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of people assessing the fire damage to the West Court Square at the corner of Fentress and North Washington Streets. Several buildings had been reduced to rubble or severely damaged.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Fires; Ruins
